---
// About section — personal story and background.
---
<section id="about" class="py-24 px-4 bg-white">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <span class="section-label text-center">About</span>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-10 text-gray-900">A bit about me</h2>
    <div class="space-y-5 text-gray-500 text-base md:text-lg leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        I got into web development around 2014, mostly by tinkering with WordPress themes. That early
        hands-on time with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript stuck with me — and gradually turned into
        something more serious.
      </p>
      <p>
        Since then, I've worked with clients, startups, and a Shopify apps company, picking up
        experience in front-end development, Shopify theme customization, cart and app integration
        troubleshooting, and client-facing technical support.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days, I enjoy working on the kinds of problems that sit at the edge of technical and
        communicative — whether that's debugging a cart drawer conflict, customizing an upsell app
        behavior, or turning a confusing error into a clear explanation a merchant can actually act on.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm also interested in building useful things on the side: tools, guides, and resources for
        developers and merchants who run into the same front-end and Shopify issues I've spent time
        solving.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>